                android:text="1. Preheat the Oven:

Preheat your oven to 400°F (200°C).
2. Prepare the Branzino:

Rinse the branzino under cold water and pat them dry with paper towels.

Score the sides of the branzino with 2-3 diagonal cuts on each side. This helps the fish cook more evenly and allows the flavors to penetrate.

Season the branzino inside and out with salt and black pepper.

Brush the branzino with olive oil, ensuring they are well-coated.

3. Roast the Branzino:

Place the branzino on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.

Roast in the preheated oven for about 20-25 minutes or until the fish is cooked through and easily flakes with a fork.

4. Prepare the Caper Butter:

While the branzino is roasting, prepare the caper butter. In a small bowl, mix together softened butter, chopped capers, fresh lemon juice, chopped parsley, salt, and black pepper. Adjust the seasoning to taste.
5. Serve:

Once the branzino is done roasting, transfer them to serving plates.

Spoon a generous amount of caper butter over each branzino.

Garnish with additional fresh parsley if desired.

6. Enjoy:

Serve the roasted branzino with caper butter immediately. This dish pairs well with a side of roasted vegetables, a simple green salad, or your favorite side dishes."
